01/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Mate Tadic was elected chairman of the BiH Constitutional Court during Friday's (30 May) court session.
Members also approved the nominations of Qazim Sadikovic, Miodrag Simovic and Tudor Pantiru as deputy chairmen of the institution.
The Office of the High Representative, meanwhile, is urging Republika Srpska to nominate a Bosnian Serb representative, so that the composition of the court can be completed.
In other news Friday, a new border crossing opened at Strmice, on the BiH-Croatian border.
(FENA, BBC, PBS BiH, BH Radio 1 - 30/05/03)
